Iavan Pijoos, News24Police on the scene at Rocking the Daisies where a staff member drowned. (News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Rocking the Daisies on Saturday confirmed the drowning of a staff member at the festival."First and foremost, we want to extend our sympathies to the individual, who was a staff member of one of the event's suppliers, and to his family," PR Representative Darryn Lee said."We can confirm that at approximately 10:50 on October 7 a drowning occurred at the venue's dam."&nbsp;Lee said the incident was picked up by the on-site lifeguards who acted swiftly.On Friday, Western Cape police said they were searching for 21-year-old man."The identity of the man cannot be released at this stage," Lieutenant-Colonel Andre Traut said at the time.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.